## Verification command

Before claiming any UI work done, run:

```bash
./gradlew detekt lint
```

This catches arbitrary `dp`/`sp`/`Color` literals, banned gradients, filler copy, buzzwords, and infinite-decoration animations. Both tasks must exit 0.

## Component anatomy

See `~/.claude/skills/ui-android/component-anatomy.md` for exact dimensions per composable (Button, TextField, Card, ListItem, TopAppBar, NavigationBar, FAB, ModalBottomSheet, AlertDialog, Snackbar, empty-state, loading, error). Touch targets ≥ 48dp, edge-to-edge always on, predictive back honored.

## Copy voice

See `~/.claude/skills/ui-android/copy-voice.md`. Sentence case for buttons (Material 3 default — never Title Case). No lorem ipsum, no "Lightning fast / Powered by AI" filler. If real copy is missing, STOP and ask the user.

## Adding new tokens

If you need a value that doesn't exist in the theme files: STOP. Ask the user to extend the theme. NEVER add arbitrary values inline.
